he researchers had created themselves.</p>\\n\\n<p>They called these articles “placebo” fake news articles.</p>\\n\\n<p>They surveyed people and asked them if they could recall seeing the article in question reported or discussed prior to the election. &nbsp;</p>\\n\\n<p>The researchers found that some participants claimed they had heard the “placebo” articles mentioned during the election season. &nbsp;</p>\\n\\n<p>*However, the study also indicated* that “most widely circulated hoaxes were seen by only a small fraction of Americans” (Crawford).</p>\\n\\n<p>Despite the narrow viewership of fake news articles, they do have the &nbsp;power to influence at least some readers’ beliefs and possibly influence those readers’ actions. &nbsp;</p>\\n\"}','{\"checkAnswerButton\":\"Check\",\"tryAgainButton\":\"Retry\",\"showSolutionButton\":\"Show solution\",\"score\":\"You got @score of @total points\",\"behaviour\":{\"enableRetry\":true,\"enableSolutionsButton\":true},\"correctAnswer\":\"Correct!\",\"incorrectAnswer\":\"Incorrect!\",\"missedAnswer\":\"Missed!\",\"displaySolutionDescription\":\"Task is updated to contain the solution.\",\"taskDescription\":\"<p>Choose the signal phrase in the following passage.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\",\"textField\":\"<p>Although most people are confident that they could not be fooled by a fake news article, research shows evidence to the contrary. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Economists Hunt Allcott and Matthew Gentzkow conducted an experiment to see if people believed fake articles that the researchers had created themselves.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>They called these articles \\u201cplacebo\\u201d fake news articles.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>They surveyed people and asked them if they could recall seeing the article in question reported or discussed prior to the election. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>The researchers found that some participants claimed they had heard the \\u201cplacebo\\u201d articles mentioned during the election season. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>*However, the study also indicated* that \\u201cmost widely circulated hoaxes were seen by only a small fraction of Americans\\u201d (Crawford).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Despite the narrow viewership of fake news articles, they do have the &nbsp;power to influence at least some readers\\u2019 beliefs and possibly influence those readers\\u2019 actions. &nbsp;<\\/p>\\n\"}','mark-the-words','div',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,'2017-05-09 23:51:51','2017-05-09 23:51:51',1,'Drag the Words',14,'{\"taskDescription\":\"<p>What are the colors of these berries when they are ripe?</p>\\n\",\"checkAnswer\":\"Check\",\"tryAgain\":\"Retry\",\"showSolution\":\"Show Solution\",\"score\":\"Score : @score of @total.\",\"behaviour\":{\"enableRetry\":true,\"enableSolutionsButton\":true,\"instantFeedback\":false},\"textField\":\"Blueberries are *blue:Check the name of the berry!*.\\nStrawberries are *red*.\\nCloudberries are *orange*.\"}','{\"taskDescription\":\"<p>What are the colors of these berries when they are ripe?<\\/p>\\n\",\"checkAnswer\":\"Check\",\"tryAgain\":\"Retry\",\"showSolution\":\"Show Solution\",\"score\":\"Score : @score of @total.\",\"behaviour\":{\"enableRetry\":true,\"enableSolutionsButton\":true,\"instantFeedback\":false},\"textField\":\"Blueberries are *blue:Check the name of the berry!*.\\nStrawberries are *red*.\\nCloudberries are *orange*.\"}','drag-the-words','div',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'2017-05-10 00:09:46','2017-05-10 00:12:19',1,'Identify the Logical Fallacy',14,'{\"taskDescription\":\"Drag the words into the correct boxes\",\"checkAnswer\":\"Check\",\"tryAgain\":\"Retry\",\"showSolution\":\"Show solution\",\"score\":\"You got @score of @total points\",\"behaviour\":{\"enableRetry\":true,\"enableSolutionsButton\":true,\"instantFeedback\":true},\"textField\":\"Because the last words spoken by either the pilot or co-pilot were “Good night, Malaysia Three-Seven-Zero,” the pilot fell asleep and accidentally crashed the plane into the ocean. *Post hoc*\\n\\nSeveral media sources reported Captain Shah was under investigation, so he must have been the individual who caused the crash. *Bandwagon*\\n\\nTransportation officials are warning the public to avoid flying over the Indian Ocean as this crash may have been the first of many. *Slippery Slope*\\n\\nMalaysian government officials are corrupt, so they don’t have any real interest in finding the real cause of the crash. *Ad hominem*\\n\\nFlight 370 and Flight 17 were both Malaysia Airlines flights in 2014 that resulted in the death or disappearance of all passengers.  It is unsafe to fly Malaysian Airlines. *Hasty generalization*\\n\\nResponding to a reporter’s accusation that the investigation was proceeding too slowly, the Prime Minister of Malaysia remarked, “I resent your implication that we are somehow covering our tracks.  My administration has an unblemished record of transparency.” *Straw man*\\n\\nMalaysia Airlines Flight 370 was the result of a conspiracy because all airlines crashes have some elements of conspiracy. *Begging the Question*\\n\\nThe disappearance of Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 was the result of either terrorism or mechanical failure. *False Dichotomy*\"}','{\"taskDescription\":\"Drag the words into the correct boxes\",\"checkAnswer\":\"Check\",\"tryAgain\":\"Retry\",\"showSolution\":\"Show solution\",\"score\":\"You got @score of @total points\",\"behaviour\":{\"enableRetry\":true,\"enableSolutionsButton\":true,\"instantFeedback\":true},\"textField\":\"Because the last words spoken by either the pilot or co-pilot were \\u201cGood night, Malaysia Three-Seven-Zero,\\u201d the pilot fell asleep and accidentally crashed the plane into the ocean. *Post hoc*\\n\\nSeveral media sources reported Captain Shah was under investigation, so he must have been the individual who caused the crash. *Bandwagon*\\n\\nTransportation officials are warning the public to avoid flying over the Indian Ocean as this crash may have been the first of many. *Slippery Slope*\\n\\nMalaysian government officials are corrupt, so they don\\u2019t have any real interest in finding the real cause of the crash. *Ad hominem*\\n\\nFlight 370 and Flight 17 were both Malaysia Airlines flights in 2014 that resulted in the death or disappearance of all passengers. \\u00a0It is unsafe to fly Malaysian Airlines. *Hasty generalization*\\n\\nResponding to a reporter\\u2019s accusation that the investigation was proceeding too slowly, the Prime Minister of Malaysia remarked, \\u201cI resent your implication that we are somehow covering our tracks. \\u00a0My administration has an unblemished record of transparency.\\u201d *Straw man*\\n\\nMalaysia Airlines Flight 370 was the result of a conspiracy because all airlines crashes have some elements of conspiracy. *Begging the Question*\\n\\nThe disappearance of Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 was the result of either terrorism or mechanical failure. *False Dichotomy*\"}','identify-the-logical-fallacy','div',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(6,'2017-05-10 00:50:10','2017-05-10 00:50:10',1,'Evaluate Logical Fallacies',16,'{\"choices\":[{\"subContentId\":\"1d4e4db3-067d-4665-b116-ecdd9aaf5bce\",\"question\":\"<p>I am a smoker, and I have a lot of friends who are smokers, and we all agree that this policy should be overturned.<br>\\n&nbsp;</p>\\n\",\"answers\":[\"<p>Bandwagon</p>\\n\",\"<p>Straw Man</p>\\n\",\"<p>Slippery Slop</p>\\n\",\"<p>No fallacy.</p>\\n\"]},{\"subContentId\":\"1040a914-1f52-41fe-a486-508c3832f19c\",\"question\":\"<p>This policy is framed in terms of health outcomes and promoting individual well-being, but the University has not instituted policies regarding many other behaviors related to health such as exercising.<br>\\n&nbsp;</p>\\n\",\"answers\":[\"<p>No Fallacy</p>\\n\",\"<p>Begging the question</p>\\n\",\"<p>Hasty generalization</p>\\n\",\"<p>Post hoc</p>\\n\"]},{\"subContentId\":\"053d3750-239a-4a06-9cac-d98c1090e8da\",\"question\":\"<p>Smoking is a right, and Americans have rights, so the smoking ban is wrong.<br>\\n&nbsp;</p>\\n\",\"answers\":[\"<p>Begging the question</p>\\n\",\"<p>False dichotomy</p>\\n\",\"<p>Straw man</p>\\n\",\"<p>No fallacy.&nbsp;</p>\\n\"]},{\"subContentId\":\"c7f02b4e-3e07-4085-b3cc-205c73f0cf5a\",\"question\":\"<p>What’s next? &nbsp;Will we ban potato chips and Cokes on campus? &nbsp;Will we force-feed broccoli and carrots to first-year students? <br>\\n&nbsp;</p>\\n\",\"answers\":[\"<p>Slippery Slope</p>\\n\",\"<p>Ad hominem</p>\\n\",\"<p>Bandwagon</p>\\n\",\"<p>No fallacy.&nbsp;</p>\\n\"]},{\"subContentId\":\"aae0b5d5-f287-4da6-a98b-cf76c5ecfaa0\",\"question\":\"<p>People eighteen years old and up are adults and have the ability to make their own decisions regarding their health and habits. That type of language asks students and faculty to be informants against each other. A college campus is a place for free expression of ideas and behaviors. </p>\\n\",\"answers\":[\"<p>No fallacy.&nbsp;</p>\\n\",\"<p>Ad hominem.</p>\\n\",\"<p>Post hoc.</p>\\n\",\"<p>Straw man</p>\\n\"]},{\"subContentId\":\"50ebf660-b87d-4db2-a10d-b2552c1544da\",\"question\":\"<p>It’s simple: &nbsp;either we are a freedom-loving campus or we aren’t? &nbsp;I choose freedom, and I believe all of America’s veterans would agree with me.&nbsp;Perhaps the Chancellor has an ulterior motive for instituting the ban and is using smokers as a scapegoat. </p>\\n\",\"answers\":[\"<p>Ad hominem </p>\\n\",\"<p>Hasty generalization</p>\\n\",\"<p>Slippery Slope</p>\\n\",\"<p>No fallacy.&nbsp;</p>\\n\"]}],\"behaviour\":{\"timeoutCorrect\":2000,\"timeoutWrong\":3000,\"soundEffectsEnabled\":false,\"enableRetry\":true,\"enableSolutionsButton\":true,\"passPercentage\":100},\"l10n\":{\"resultSlideTitle\":\"You got :numcorrect of :maxscore correct\",\"showSolutionButtonLabel\":\"Show solution\",\"retryButtonLabel\":\"Retry\",\"solutionViewTitle\":\"Solution\",\"correctText\":\"Correct!\",\"incorrectText\":\"Incorrect!\",\"muteButtonLabel\":\"Mute feedback sound\",\"closeButtonLabel\":\"Close\",\"slideO